summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackNYX Professional Makeup Face Glue Gripping Primer hydrates and grips your makeup for 24 hrs without the ick! Get all the grip, none of the stickiness.
details: DetailsFeaturesFoundation GLUED! Powder GLUED! Blush GLUED! Your makeup is about to get stuck like glue!Formulated with Polyglutamic Acid and Maple Syrup, this primer drenches your skin in hydration, and grips your makeup without the ick for up 24 hours!This non-comedogenic primer feels comfy on the skin, breathable all day, and gives a soft-focus finish. GLUE it to me!Water-based primer that is compatible with all skin types, including sensitive skinKey IngredientsPolyglutamic Acid for extreme hydrationMaple Syrup keeps makeup gripped all day longItem 2627969How To UseStep One: Prime skin with The Face Glue Primer. Spread a dime-sized amount of product evenly on the face and see the transformation as the white gel blends seamlessly with no cast into all skin tones! No need to wait! Just stick the rest of your makeup right on top!Step Two: Set with The Face Glue Setting Spray!Step Three: Stick those brows down with The Brow Glue! Get into ALL of this glue!IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Glycerin, PEG-150 Distearate, Butylene Glycol, PVP, Opuntia Ficus-Indica Stem Extract, Acer Saccharum Extract / Sugar Maple Extract, Potassium PCA, Carbomer, Isododecane, Sodium Hyaluronate, Tromethamine, Aluminum Hydroxide, Magnesium PCA, Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate, Hydroxypropyltrimonium Hyaluronate, Caprylyl Glycol, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Xanthan Gum, Panthenol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Polyglutamic Acid, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Octyldodecanol, Tocopherol, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Potassium Sorbate, Phenoxyethanol, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Rating: ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÜ (4.5/5)

NYX Cosmetics has done it again with The Face Glue Primer, a product designed to give your makeup that much-needed grip for all-day wear. As a makeup enthusiast constantly on the lookout for effective base products, I was eager to test this primer's claims, and it did not disappoint.

**Packaging:**  
The Face Glue Primer comes in a sleek, compact tube that's easy to use and travel-friendly. The flip-top cap allows for precise dispensing, ensuring that you can control the amount of product you apply. The minimalist design aligns well with NYX's youthful and contemporary branding.

**Application:**  
The primer has a lightweight and slightly tacky texture that feels smooth as you apply it to the skin. It spreads easily and a little goes a long way, so you won't need to use much to achieve a good base. I used it both with brushes and my fingertips, and it worked beautifully with either method.

**Performance:**  
What sets The Face Glue Primer apart is its ability to create a strong, adhesive base for makeup. I tested it during a long day that included work, errands, and an evening out, and my foundation held up impressively. It provided that extra grip, preventing my makeup from sliding off or fading, and it even helped blur imperfections, giving my skin a smoother appearance.

I noticed that my makeup looked more vibrant and fresh throughout the day, which is a huge plus. I typically have combination skin, and I was pleased that the primer didn't exacerbate any dry patches or make my T-zone overly oily.

**Texture and Finish:**  
The tacky finish of the primer seems a bit unusual initially, but it absolutely helps in keeping everything in place once foundation is applied. The finish is not overly matte, allowing for a more natural look that still provides longevity.

**Scent:**  
The Face Glue Primer has a light, pleasant scent that isn't overpowering. It dissipates quickly after application, making it suitable for those sensitive to fragrance.

**Value for Money:**  
In terms of price, this primer is relatively affordable, especially considering its effectiveness. NYX delivers quality at a great price point, and this product exemplifies that philosophy.

**Conclusion:**  
NYX Cosmetics The Face Glue Primer is a solid addition to any makeup routine, particularly for those seeking a reliable and long-lasting base. The grip it provides truly does elevate makeup wear, extending the life of your foundation and enhancing your overall look. 

If you want a primer that not only prepares the skin but also locks in your makeup for the day, I highly recommend giving this one a try. It's become a staple in my makeup collection, and I can't wait to continue using it for future looks. 

**Pros:**  
- Exceptional grip and longevity  
- Lightweight, easy application  
- Affordable price point  
- Suitable for various skin types  

**Cons:**  
- The tackiness may take some getting used to  
- May not provide enough hydration for extremely dry skin   

Overall, a fantastic primer that brings affordability and performance together seamlessly!
faceoff_positive.headline: Love it

faceoff_negative.comments:
The packaging of this is cute but a little gimmicky. NYX has some good primers, and this 'The Face Glue' is okay but not their best. The packaging makes it difficult to control the amount of product that is released, and because the consistency is somewhat runny, it can get messy. For a 'gripping' primer, I didn't find it to be overly tacky. It had just a little more grip than any other non-gripping primer. It is lightweight once it absorbs into the skin, it didn'tI feel uncomfortable, and compared to not using it, I noticed a difference in the longevity and evenness of how my makeup wore. It didn't change the finish of my foundation or skin tint, so I'd say it gives a natural finish. It doesn't have any scent that I can detect, which I appreciate. As far as being a great gripping primer- no, this won't have things sticking to your face, but for a being a good general primer- yes, my makeup looked better & lasted longer with it. 
*I received this product for free in exchange for my review, all opinions are honest and are my own*
